ZCZC EE42
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 272300 UTC
ON FRIDAY EVENING SLOW MOV HIGH PRESSURE 1035 IS EXP TO BE CENTRED OVER
NERN ENGLAND. THIS HIGH IS THE DOMINANT FEATURE ACROSS UK AND SURROUNDING
WATERS. THROUGH THE WEEKEND THE HIGH IS EXP TO DECLINE AS A SMALL SHALLOW
AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 1015 S OF ICELAND DRIFTS E THEN S OVER THE NW OF
BRITAIN. HOWEVER THE LOW IS EXP TO GRADUALLY FILL AND LOSE ITS IDENTITY
ON SUNDAY. BY MONDAY A RIDGE BUILDS TO THE W OF THE BRITISH ISLES. MEANWHILE
ON SATURDAY A SECOND LOW FORMS E OF GREENLAND MOV ACROSS THE N OF SCANDINAVIA
ON SUNDAY AND MONDAY. AN ASSOCIATED FRONTAL TROUGH MAY MOV S ACROSS THE NERN
ISLES LATER MONDAY. LOC STRG WINDS MAY DEVELOP LATER IN THE PERIOD IN THE
S OF FITZROY MAINLY NEAR CAPE FINISTERRE. OTHERWISE WINDS ARE NOT EXP TO
BE HAZARDOUS ACROSS NITON THROUGH THE PERIOD
